  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "CLEANING SUPERVISOR",
  "description": "<p>The Cleaning Supervisor oversees daily cleaning operations and leads a team of cleaners to ensure all assigned areas meet required hygiene, safety, and service standards. This role includes manpower scheduling, on-site quality control, client communication, and basic documentation.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><p><strong>Operations & Quality Control</strong></p><ul><li><p>Supervise daily cleaning activities at assigned sites and ensure cleanliness standards are consistently met.</p></li><li><p>Conduct routine site inspections, identify issues, and implement corrective actions promptly.</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper cleaning methods are followed for different areas (toilets, common areas, offices, kitchens, etc.).</p></li><li><p>Ensure correct and safe use of cleaning chemicals, equipment, and tools (including proper labeling and dilution where applicable).</p></li><li><p>Maintain high service standards and ensure work is completed on time.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Manpower & Scheduling</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare duty rosters and allocate manpower according to site requirements.</p></li><li><p>Monitor attendance, punctuality, discipline, and performance of cleaning staff.</p></li><li><p>Train new staff and coach existing staff on work procedures, safety, and service standards.</p></li><li><p>Arrange replacement manpower when staff are on leave/MC or when urgent manpower gaps occur.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Client Communication</strong></p><ul><li><p>Liaise with site representatives/clients to receive feedback and handle service requests.</p></li><li><p>Address complaints professionally and escalate major issues to management when necessary.</p></li><li><p>Support special cleaning tasks or ad-hoc requests from clients.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Inventory & Documentation</strong></p><ul><li><p>Track and manage cleaning supplies, PPE, and equipment; request replenishment when needed.</p></li><li><p>Maintain basic records such as attendance logs, inspection checklists, incident reports, and equipment logs.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Safety & Compliance</strong></p><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety requirements and company SOPs.</p></li><li><p>Report hazards, incidents, or accidents immediately and implement preventive measures.</p></li></ul>",
